Request Failed — Network or CORS
The browser blocked or could not complete this request: Failed to fetch
Common causes:

CORS: the API did not return Access-Control-Allow-Origin for this origin. Browsers enforce this; the request may actually reach the server but the response is hidden from JavaScript.
Network: host unreachable, DNS failure, or offline (relevant in air-gapped networks — confirm the host resolves internally).
Mixed content: calling http:// from an https:// page.
Workarounds: use the Chrome Extension build (bypasses CORS via host permissions), run a local CORS proxy, or for throwaway testing launch Chrome with --disable-web-security --user-data-dir=%TEMP%\relaypad (never browse normally in that profile).
